President Obama issued a statement on January 30, 2009, expressing his support for the Senate's passage of bipartisan legislation to provide health insurance to children affected by the economic downturn. He emphasized the importance of ensuring that every child in America has access to affordable healthcare, especially during times of economic hardship. The legislation, which expands the Children's Health Insurance Program, was seen as a step towards the President's broader goal of ensuring quality and affordable healthcare for all Americans.